<article>
  <p>NWRUG is a Manchester-based community for people interested in the Ruby programming language. We run regular <a href="/events">events</a> open to anyone who wants to learn more about Ruby. We also have a <a href="/mailing-list">mailing list</a> where you can discuss Ruby and related topics online.</p>

  <h2 id="our-aim">Our Aim</h2>

  <p>Our aim is to help grow and support the Ruby community here in the North West. We want NWRUG to be a diverse and inclusive community that is open to all those with an interest in Ruby regardless of gender, sexual orientation, disability, appearance, race or religion. Read more about <a href="/participate">participating with NWRUG</a> and our <a href="/code-of-conduct">code of conduct</a>.</p>
</article>

